SetUP prometheus in VM & run it as a service(should be running in background):
==============================================================================
cd prometheus
./prometheus & (Command to run it as a service)
Running on the port number 9090(default port number)
vi alert_rules.yml
add the yml file inside .yml in prometheus

In prometheus.yml file we need all the rule files under rule_files:
rule_files:
  - "alert_rules.yml"



SetUp node_exporter in VM:
==========================
Install the Node Exporter & Run it as a service (That means it should be running in background)
cd node_exporter
./node_exporter & (Command to run it as a service)
Running on port 9100 (Default) & we can check the metrics with http:IP_Address:9100/metrics

Setup Alert_Manager in VM:
Install the alert_manager in VM 
In alertmanager we can add the email for getting the email notification & details(time configurations)
cd alermanager/
./alertmanager &    (Running on default number 9093 & IP_Address:9093/#/alerts Where we can see the alert groups setup we can see)
vi alertmanager.yaml   (default file)



After adding the alert_rules.yml in the prometheus.yml we need to restart it:
pgrep prometheus --> It will  give a PID --> Kill PID --> Prometheus will stopped
Immediatly we can start it again with   ./prometheus &
So it will restart it again & we check the alert rules in prometheus IP_Address:9090/rules. 
Here we can see the alert rules are visible now.

So now we can add the - alertmanager:9093 in the prometheus.yml under alertmanager configuration  
alerting:
  alertmanagers:
    - static_configs:
        - targets: 
           - 192.168.10.106:9093


